# TDMD benchmark T0 — morse-analytic dimer (lj units, identity reference).
#
# With sigma=epsilon=mass=1 the numerical values in lj are bitwise-identical
# to the metal .data above: length_lj = length_metal / sigma = length_metal,
# mass_lj = mass_metal / m_ref = mass_metal, velocity_lj = velocity_metal *
# sqrt(mass/epsilon) = velocity_metal. The two .data files differ only in this
# header comment — that is the whole point of identity-reference lj: it makes
# the metal<->lj conversion a readability-test, not a numerics test. A
# non-identity lj benchmark is deferred to T2.4 (T1 cross-check).

